{
  "answer": "**Diwan-E-Ghalib** by Mirza Ghalib, chapter 82 (\"Ibn-e-Maryam hua kare koi\").[^1]\n\nThe opening couplet is:\n\n> Let someone be the Son of Mary, great and true, what can one do?  \n> For this my sorrow, find a cure that's new, what can one do?[^2]\n\nLater in the ghazal, the couplet questioning Khizr is:\n\n> What did the guide Khizr for Alexander really do?  \n> So who is there to follow now, what can one do?[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [chapter](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/82-ibn-e-maryam-hua-kare-koi/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/82-ibn-e-maryam-hua-kare-koi/translation/#p-e38771).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/82-ibn-e-maryam-hua-kare-koi/translation/#p-c60ac6).",
